added.title: Space House Part 4
added.description: The free vacation in space was just an elaborate plot by Brainiac to collect every hero and villain in the DC Multiverse. The Titans and Superhero Girls agree to help Brainiac become an adult in exchange for letting them go.

added.title: Magic Man
added.description: In a quest to become a magic man, Beast Boy accidentally destroys Raven's spell book, so they must go find another one.

added.title: NBTS 2: Chapter Four
added.description: To retrieve the final stem, the Titans must concur a virtual world full of increasingly harder obstacles.

added.title: NBTS 2: Chapter Five
added.description: The Titans use to the stems to summon BER, but will it be enough to stop Ultralak?

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: In order to appear on a successful kids show, Nom Nom must successfully complete anger management, with Grizz as his partner.
The Baby Bears' dreams come true when they find a 100 dollar bill. But when they can't bear to spend it, they realize it's difficult to let go.

added.title: Bear Lift
added.description: To help raise money to save Darrell's store, the Bears use the stack as a taxi through a ride share app.

added.title: Bro Brawl
added.description: The Bears participate in a brother-themed game show against Panda's ex-BFF, Tom, and his roommates.

added.title: Beehive
added.description: The Bears allow bees to live in the cave to make honey. But soon the Bears, entranced by the honey, become the bees' mindless servants.

added.title: The Decisions
added.description: When everything goes wrong in Darwin's life, he begins to suspect that Gumball's bad influence might be to blame. Darwin decides to go elsewhere for guidance and finds a new mentor in Alan. But maybe it's time Darwin started making his own decisions.

added.title: The Diet
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the reason Dad's diet wasn't working was that he was actually on ten diets and eating a meal for each of them. They eventually manage to help him lose weight, but Richard's newfound buffness also brings out his more obnoxious side.

added.title: The Flakers
added.description: When Gumball is left by Darwin to get a pounding from Tina, he decides to teach Darwin a lesson.

added.title: The Fight
added.description: Anais is convinced that Gumball is being bullied by Tina Rex.

added.title: Riding the Storm Out
added.description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: Adventures in Babysitting
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max meet a family that appears to be a mirror image of them, but when Max goes off on a hike with their matriarch, Maxine, Ben is forced to babysit Simon Sez, a brat with a Billy Billions designed backpack  that turns him into a formidable robot.

added.title: Cutting Corners
added.description: Ben approaches Geezer Bob about doing a little yard work to earn spending money, but when Ben goes Upgrade to transform the lawnmower into a super fast mowing machine, he accidentally draws the ire of Bob's gnome-neighbors, the tiny, terrifyingly tenacious Billy-Bob Goblins.

added.title: Brother Builder
added.description: As Craig races against time to build a super important invention, we learn how Craig became such a clever inventor!

added.title: Jessica the Intern
added.description: Entranced with the Trading Tree and Kit's business acumen, Jessica joins Kit as her intern!

added.title: Secret in a Bottle
added.description: Craig needs to get a secret off his chest, so he pays a visit to the Keeper of Secrets in the Creek.

added.title: JPony
added.description: JP decides to follow his heart and tries to join the Horse Girls.

added.title: Doorway to Helen
added.description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

added.title: Jelly Aches
added.description: The school descends into chaos after getting a visit from Gazunga, the Jealousy Troll.

added.title: Simply Perfect
added.description: When the kids are about to be subject to school testing with no time to study, Courtney freaks and orders a Brainiac Ray from the back of a comic book that does not work as advertised.

added.title: Baby Brother Blues
added.description: When Beth is told that the impending arrival of a baby brother is about to ruin her life, she runs away to find a new family.

added.title: Space Codyty
added.description: Izzy, convinced that Cody is an alien, embarks on a journey through space to take him back home.

added.title: Snack to the Future
added.description: Owen wants his favorite treat, Jiggle Giggle, so bad that he's willing to use a time machine to get to snacktime quicker. But when he ends up stuck in the past, Owen must decide between getting home and getting fed.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple needs to acquire a lifetime supply of toilet paper to finish his modern art sculpture.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Apple tries to survive a weekend alone while taking care of Onion's plant.

added.title: Party Popper
added.description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears while trapped in a pet shop, so they can save French Fry from facing hers.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
added.description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: #MeetTheCheetah
added.description: Barbara Minerva is super-jealous of  "little Miss Perfect" Diana Prince. But when she uses an ancient artifact from her dad's collection to place a curse on Diana, it turns out that Diana's not the one who's cursed. It's Barbara.

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: When she stumbles across a villainous plot to blow up a bridge, Bumblebee shies from the challenge of taking on the baddies and reaches out to her friends. But when the other heroes are all indisposed, it'll take every ounce of courage Bumblebee has to rise to the occasion … despite being the smallest of the bunch.

added.title: #SuperWho?
added.description: Overwhelmed by the amount of Superman coverage in Metropolis, Supergirl decides to get out there and really show the city what she can do. But when Superman inadvertently puts everyone in harm's way, Supergirl has to decide whether to do what's good for the people or what's good for her ego.

added.title: Prank Call
added.description: Lion-O wants to prove to the ThunderKittens that he's not just some boring old adult, like Tygra, even if it means ignoring his instincts and messing with an obviously evil crystal.

added.title: Driller
added.description: Panthro is getting a little fed up with having to fix things around the Cats' Lair constantly, which is unfortunate because the ThunderCats are about to be attacked by an unstoppable drilling robot, and he's gonna break everything!

added.title: Secret of the Unicorn
added.description: A crying unicorn appears at the Cats' Lair and weepily tells the ThunderCats that all of her unicorn friends have been captured! Tygra thinks he's just the unicorn expert to help the last of the unicorns, he just needs her to stop sobbing long enough to tell him who took her friends. Easier said than done.

added.title: Panthro Plagiarized!
added.description: Vultureman has got a brand new invention but there's one big problem: he stole the idea from Panthro! Oh, also Vultureman is using his invention to take over Third Earth. So, there are two big problems.

added.title: Warrior Maiden Invasion
added.description: Third Earth is being overrun by super tough, super buff Warrior Maidens and it looks like the ThunderCats are next on their hit list! It's gonna be up to the ThunderKittens to save the day even though the kittens are so small and the Warrior Maidens are so big.

added.title: Lars of the Stars
added.description: Lars rises to the occasion.

added.title: Jungle Moon
added.description: Stevonnie finds themself alone on an adventure.

added.title: Your Mother and Mine
added.description: Steven takes Garnet to meet some of his new friends.

added.title: The Big Show
added.description: Steven shoots a documentary that follows a local band as they get their first big break.

added.title: Pool Hopping
added.description: Garnet and Steven explore the most unlikely timelines in Beach City.

added.title: Sleeper Sofa
added.description: When the Sky Pirates infiltrate Sheriff HQ, they put our heroes in danger!

added.title: Mao Mao's Nakey
added.description: When MM loses his clothes while trying to scale the Ruby Pure Heart, he has to get back to Sheriff's HQ by daybreak.

added.title: Food Chain
added.description: On a field trip to the Candy Kingdom Museum of Natural History, Finn and Jake learn about the food chain by becoming the food chain!

added.title: Furniture & Meat
added.description: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

added.title: Nemesis
added.description: A shadowy figure named Peace Master targets the Candy Kingdom elite.

added.title: Ghost Fly
added.description: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful spectre.

added.title: Chips & Ice Cream
added.description: BMO's favorite entertainers unexpectedly find a new home at the tree house.

added.title: Late Night Talky Time
added.description: The moon is bored of taking the nightshift, since everyone's always asleep. So Unikitty leads the gang in putting on an over-the-top late night talk show to keep the moon occupied.

added.title: Welcome to the Unikingdom
added.description: After Unikitty finds out that tourism is down in the Unikingdom, she recruits the gang to make a tourism video to inspire people to visit the kingdom. But after calamities come one after another, Unikitty begins to think the video is going to turn out to be a disaster. However the friends save the day with some creativity and manage to get a single tourist to visit. Mission accomplished!

added.title: Time Capsule
added.description: The gang puts their favorite items in a Time Capsule to send 100 years in the future, but they get stuck inside right before the door seals. Dr Fox tries to convince the gang to let her use their favorite items to escape the capsule, and each character tells a story about why their favorite item is their favorite, and why Dr Fox can't destroy it to escape. Finally it's revealed that Unikitty's favorite thing was friendship and she trapped everyone in the capsule on purpose, so the future could see their friendship! Unfortunately for the gang, even after they surrender their favorite items to escape, it doesn't work and they have to wait 100 years to finally leave the capsule.

added.title: Music Videos
added.description: Unikitty hosts a live music video countdown show for the kingdom, presenting the ecstatic audience with the top 4 music videos in the Unikingdom, featuring our favorite characters. Unikitty & Hawkodile team up for a death-metal picnic battle video, Dr Fox sings an 80s synth-pop jam about creating the perfect dance partner with science, Puppycorn sings a ridiculous nonsense song about his perfect day, and Richard unexpectedly closes the show out with the best song in the kingdom, a blistering hair-metal rock ballad with lots of solos and passionate dancing.

added.title: Brock Most Wanted
added.description: When Master Frown starts ruining parties to earn a promotion from his bosses, the Doom Lords, Brock accidentally gets blamed for the calamity. He helps Frown ruin more parties to clear his name and prove he's not the real party pooper, but before long Brock is the most notorious criminal in the kingdom, and the Doom Lords hire him as Master Party Pooper. Desperate to get his promotion and save his friend, Master Frown recruits Unikitty to ruin one last party, Brock's Doom Lord initiation ceremony.

added.title: Two Lies, One Truth
added.description: As Lloyd unmasks Mystake for who she truly is, Emperor Garmadon embraces Harumi as his daughter of darkness. Meanwhile, Wu holds onto faith as he leads his friends into dangerous Oni territory in the hope of finding Firstbourne's nest

added.title: Dos mentiras una verdad
added.description: Cuando Lloyd desenmascara y revela la identidad de Mystake, el Emperador Garmadon acepta a Harumi como su hija de la oscuridad. Mientras tanto, Wu se aferra a su fe al llevar a sus amigos hacia territorios Oni peligrosos esperando encontrar el nido de la Primogénita.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: El eslabon mas debil
added.description: Lloyd le paga con la misma moneda a Harumi para quitarle el poder a su padre, y los Ninjas aprenden lo que se necesita para ser un Cazador de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Weakest Link
added.description: Lloyd turns the tables on Harumi to take his father's power away, and the Ninja learn what it takes to be a Dragon Hunter.

added.title: Salvando a Faith
added.description: Lloyd y su equipo planean tomar el control del Oni Titan. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, los Ninja caen en las garras del Barón de Hierro y un viejo maestro regresa.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Saving Faith
added.description: Lloyd and his team plot to take control of the Oni Titan. Meanwhile in the First Realm, the Ninja fall into Iron Baron's clutches and an old master returns.

added.title: Lessons for a Master
added.description: When Iron Baron forces Wu to retrieve the Dragon Armor, things don't go as planned. In Ninjago, Lloyd can only endure so much as he holds onto hope for the Ninjas' return.

added.title: Lecciones para un maestro
added.description: Cuando el Barón de Hierro obliga a Wu a tomar la Armadura de Dragón, las cosas no salen como se planearon. En Ninjago, hay un límite de lo que Lloyd puede soportar mientras se aferra a la esperanza del regreso de los Ninjas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Destino verde
added.description: Los Ninjas regresan por fin a casa y se unen para detener al Emperador Garmadon, obligando a Lloyd a tomar una decisión que cambiará por siempre a Ninjago.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Green Destiny
added.description: The Ninja finally return home and unite to stop Emperor Garmadon, forcing Lloyd to make a decision that will forever change Ninjago.

added.title: Every Meat Burritos
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and Fives want Every Meat Burritos from the Jimbros' Burritos drive-thru.

added.title: Lars de las estrellas
added.description: Lars demuestra estar a la altura.

added.title: Selva lunar
added.description: Stevonnie se encuentra solo en una aventura.

added.title: Tu mama y la mia
added.description: Steven lleva a Garnet a conocer a algunos de sus nuevos amigos.

added.title: El gran espectaculo
added.description: Steven filma un documental que sigue los pasos de una banda local mientras consiguen su primer gran oportunidad.

added.title: De laguna en laguna
added.description: Garnet y Steven exploran las líneas de tiempo más improbables de Ciudad Playa.

added.title: Dodge This
added.description: The park guys want to win a dodge ball tournament.

added.title: Journey to the Bottom of the Crash Pit
added.description: The guys need to get the park video camera at the bottom of the crash pit.

added.title: Expert or Liar
added.description: Rigby wants to redeem himself by winning on "Expert or Liar."

added.title: Catching the Wave
added.description: Pops wants to catch a wave.

added.title: Nano of the North
added.description: It's raining in Townville, but this is more than just rain. These drops are actually microscopic robots tearing apart the city, and the girls must find a way to fight them on their own level.

added.title: Manejo de la ira
added.description: Para participar de un exitoso programa para niños, Nom Nom debe superar con éxito la prueba de manejo de la ira, con Pardo como compañero.
Los sueños de los Osos bebés se hacen realidad cuando encuentran un billete de 100 dólares. Pero cuando no soportan la idea de gastarlo, se dan cuenta de lo difícil que es desprenderse.

added.title: Viaje con Osos
added.description: Para ayudar a recaudar dinero para salvar la tienda de Darrell, los Osos usan el tronco como taxi a través de una aplicación de viajes compartidos.

added.title: Lucha Fraternal
added.description: Los Osos participan de un programa de juegos para hermanos contra los ex mejores amigos de Panda: Tom y sus compañeros de casa.

added.title: El panal
added.description: Los Osos permiten que unas abejas vivan en la cueva para hacer miel. Pero pronto, los Osos, embelesados por la miel, se convieten en los sirvientes automatizados de las abejas.

added.title: Criss Cross Crisis
added.description: Another one of the Professor's plans goes awry when he tries to switch apples for oranges causing the entire town to switch from one body to another. The girls must remedy the situation.

added.title: Lord Vaquero Darrell
added.description: Todos se ven obligados a enfrentar grandes cambios en Boxmore.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Lord Cowboy Darrell
added.description: Everyone is forced to deal with some major changes at Boxmore.

added.title: To Balderly Go
added.description: Prohyas is crushed when his good hair day becomes a no hair day and Vambre has to battle a furry monster alone while her bro is in shock without his locks!

added.title: Body Trouble
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Belly Bag have a disagreement, they separate and try to make each other jealous.

added.title: Shower Party
added.description: Things get out of hand when Andrew W. K. helps Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus throw a party while Uncle Grandpa is in the shower.

added.title: Winning at Whining
added.description: Vambre's challenge to Prohyas: Don't whine for the entirety of the next mission and you can have the Magisword we get at the end.

added.title: Veamos el Show de Boxmore
added.description: Nuestros héroes descubren que las grabaciones de la cámara de seguridad de Boxmore son la cosa más divertida del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Let's Watch the Boxmore Show
added.description: Our heroes discover that the Boxmore security camera feed is the most entertaining thing ever.

added.title: Changeable Terraingable
added.description: Personality conflicts between Vambre and Prohyas come to a head as the Warriors miraculously manage to ace a mission at an ever changing labyrinth.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's number one fan gets more than he bargained for when Uncle Grandpa overstays his welcome.

added.title: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohyas Warrior!
added.description: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

added.title: Ultimate Weapon
added.description: When Max finds out that part of an alien weapon has been unearthed in Texas, he becomes obsessed with finding it. In doing so, he leads Ben and Gwen on a wild adventure.

added.title: Vambre's Guilty Pleasure
added.description: Vambre tries her best to keep her tough Warrior reputation intact and still go to the cutesy wootsy Piggiepie Jones stage show.

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
added.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

added.title: The Great Spaghetti Western
added.description: Mr. Gus repeatedly runs afoul of a crooked mayor while winning the hears of the townsfolk.

added.title: Mystery Sleepover
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad attempt to solve a mystery.

added.title: Monster Party
added.description: Enid is faced with a choice when her old friends from Ghoul School show up.

added.title: Birdman
added.description: When Birdman makes the RV's attic his new home, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to make him leave before they're all driven crazy.

added.title: OK A.U.!
added.description: An evil warlock takes our heroes to a strange alternate universe.

added.title: Videos musicales
added.description: Unikitty conduce un programa de videos musicales, presentando a la eufórica audiencia los cuatro mejores videos musicales del Unireino protagonizados por nuestros personajes favoritos.

added.title: Pijamada Misteriosa
added.description: KO, Enid y Rad intentan resolver un misterio.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Capsula del tiempo
added.description: La banda pone sus objetos favoritos dentro de una capsula del tiempo para enviarlas 100 años al futuro, pero quedan atrapados dentro antes de que la puerta se cierre.

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: El Padre Prodigo
added.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

added.title: Ninjago Confidencial
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

added.title: Se busca Brock
added.description: Cuando Master Frown comienza a arruinar fiestas para ganar un ascenso de sus jefes, los Señores de la Muerte, Brock accidentalmente es culpado por las desgracias.

added.title: Charlas Nocturnas
added.description: La luna está aburrida de tomar el turno de noche, ya que todos siempre están dormidos. Entonces, Unikitty lidera a la pandilla en la presentación de un programa de entrevistas nocturno exagerado para mantener la luna ocupada.

added.title: El secreto en la botella
added.description: Craig necesita compartir un secreto con alguien, por lo que visita al Guardián de los Secretos en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Fiesta de Monstruos
added.description: Enid debe tomar una decisión cuando llegan sus antiguos amigos de la Escuela de monstruos.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Bienvenidos al Unireino
added.description: Después de descubrir que el turismo escasea en el Unireino, Unikitty recluta a la banda para que hagan un video que inspire a la gente a visitar el reino. Pero luego de varias calamidades, Unikitty comienza a creer que el video resultará siendo un desastre. Sin embargo, los amigos salvan el día con algo de creatividad y logran hacer que un solo turista los visite. iMisión cumplida!

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: El Templo de la Locura
added.description: Jay debe enfrentarse solo a Unagami en el juego final, pero Unagami tiene una batalla más grande al enfrentarse a la verdad sobre su propia identidad.

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: Money Broom Wizard
added.description: Can Clarence, Jeff and Sumo manage to have a good time at "Pizza Swamp" Arcade with only one dollar to spend between them? Yes.

added.title: Sobreviviendo A La Tormenta
added.description: El campamento de Ben y Gwen se ve interrumpido por los gélidos Weatherheads -Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o-, pero un Omnitrix que funciona mal y dispara un montón de extraterrestres podría no ser un pronóstico de éxito.

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: #ConoceAGuepardo
added.description: Barbara Minerva está super celosa de la "pequeña señorita perfecta" Diana Prince. Pero cuando usa un antiguo artefacto de la colección de su padre para lanzar una maldición contra Diana, la maldición se vuelve en su contra.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Shhh
added.description: Mientras Ben se relaja en un monasterio con una política de silencio, no puede quedarse callado y, por accidente, despierta a un peligroso Dragón oculto en una recámara secreta bajo los salones sagrados...una tarea que podría ser demasiado para manejar, iincluso para Diamante!

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: Cuando tropieza con un malvado complot para hacer explotar un puente de la ciudad, Bumblebee se espanta y acude a sus amigas para que derroten a los malhechores. Pero cuando todas sus super amigas están ocupadas, Bumblebee debe buscar cada gramo de coraje en ella para hacer frente a la situación, a pesar de ser la más pequeña del grupo.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: La Breve Carrera De La Nina Suertuda
added.description: Cuando un hechicero jugador de cosplay pone las manos sobre una varita mágica real en la convención Comic Con, Ben consigue la ayuda de Gwen para impedir que Hex la recupere: Gwen engaña al hechicero malvado y le hace creer que es una poderosa maga...ila única e inimitable Niña Suertuda!

added.title: Duo Espinoso
added.description: Después de dejar Pequeña Escuela Madre, Steven ha encontrado un nuevo pasatiempo: las plantas.

added.title: #SuperQuien
added.description: Abrumada por la cantidad de cobertura que Superman recibe en las noticias de Metrópolis, Supergirl decide mostrarle a la ciudad lo que puede hacer. Pero cuando Superman pone a todos en peligro sin querer, Supergirl debe decidir si hacer lo que es correcto para la gente o para ella misma.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Home on the Run/Top Slot
added.description: Home on the Run: We are introduced to Shun's mysterious backstory, his relationship with his industrialist father and desire for a closer knit family./Top Slot: Dan and Shun butt heads on how best to make the AO a real team amidst growing threats including the mysterious Shargo Ronin.

added.title: Aventuras Cuidando Ninos
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max se encuentran con una familia que parece ser un reflejo de ellos. Pero cuando Max sale a caminar con su matriarca, Maxine, Ben se ve obligado a cuidar a Simon Sez, un malcriado con una mochila diseñada por Billy Billones, que lo convierte en un robot formidable.

added.title: Bobbie Not Blobby
added.description: Axel discovers that the culprit behind Bobbie Blobby's missing mech-suit is Masko, who only wanted to clean out its clogged clay cannons, but lets the suit fall into the hands (or tentacles) of Dr. Nautilus - intent on flooding the sewers!

added.title: Fathers and Friends/Midsummer Nightmare
added.description: Midsummer Nightmare: Drago and the other AO Bakugan face an unseen threat with earth shattering power only to be left wondering if it was all a dream./Father's and Fiends: Osamu Kazami comes to take his son Shun back home and finds a defiance he hadn't counted on.

added.title: Sand Trap
added.description: Axel and the team take to the desert dunes of a playground sandbox as Madcap attempts to unearth an army of Spy Lizards from the same line as Galileo!

added.title: Dawn Before Dusk
added.description: Dawn Before Dusk, Part 1: The AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become much, much larger./Dawn Before Dusk, Part 2: Benton Dusk reveals that the AO have been indentified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

added.title: I.C.E. (In Case of Emergency)
added.description: When Ice Man decides to be a hero, Mega Man, influenced by Ice Man's literalness, steps down from the hero biz until a true crisis snaps him out of it.

added.title: Dodge City
added.description: Axel embraces the spirit of dodgeball to stop Madcap and Princess SugarSalt's battle over who is the better villain from spilling over into Zoe and Cleo's argument over who is the better coach!

added.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
added.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

added.title: Trust Your Guts, Man!
added.description: Guts Man tries to undo Dr. Light's eco-friendly disposal of trash in Silicon City by infiltrating the family and destroying the Lighthouse so he can eat it!

added.title: The Best Team
added.description: When Madcap and his minions crash a soapbox derby, the team must stop the baddies and help Axel - stuck in a car with Luka - cross the finish line!

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Drill of the Hunt
added.description: Mega Man tries a quick fix using Hypno Woman's powers to rehabilitate Drill Man, to disastrous results!

added.title: Joyride
added.description: At a rummage sale with Uncle Andrew, Axel and Zoe must stop Madcap from turning her long-lost tank toy, Joyride, into an agent of mayhem!

added.title: Power Cycle
added.description: After replicating Elec Man's powers, an underslept/overcharged Mega Man goes on a 24/7 hero spree that ends up turning him into his own worst enemy.

added.title: Bored to Be Wild
added.description: Mega Man teams up with his crush, Ashley Adderley, to solve a series of science riddles left by Chemical Man, who's plotting to turn all the city's metal into rubber.

added.title: Nature Clarence
added.description: Clarence, Sumo and Jeff's nature hike veers off course courtesy of their under qualified, overwhelmed guide Josh, prompting Clarence to take the lead.

added.title: J-Pony
added.description: JP decide seguir su corazón y trata de unirse a las Chicas Ecuestres.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Huyendo de Casa
added.description: Descubriremos el misterioso pasado de Shun, su relación con su padre (un magnate de la industria), y su deseo por tener una familia más unida.

added.title: Un Verdadero Lider
added.description: Entre diversas amenazas, como el misterioso Shargo Ronin, Dan y Shun no pueden acordar la mejor forma de convertir a Los Fantásticos en un verdadero equipo.

added.title: Portal hacia Helen
added.description: Craig hace una conexión a larga distancia con un niño que ama el Arroyo tanto como él.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Pesadilla de Verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y Amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Pilot Expansion
added.description: Clarence, Sumo, and Jeff reminisce about the day they first met - although a few of the details are foggy.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos conocen a Benton Dusk y descubren que su pequeño mundo está a punto de volverse mucho más grande.

added.title: Patients
added.description: Clarence must somehow navigate the mind-numbing boredom of a doctor's office waiting room to earn the ultimate prize - candy from the reception desk candy jar.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 2
added.description: Benton Dusk revela que Los Fantásticos son considerados personas de interés por poderosas corporaciones como AAAnimus.

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: Nothing Ventured
added.description: Clarence and Sumo look to throw together some quick cash so they can invest in Chad and Sumo's dad's new business venture, a boutique sculpture shop.

added.title: Aventura en el Laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: Atrapados en la Jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Demonios Internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: Banda de por Vida
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val acompañan a Xochi a un concierto punk, quieren demostrar que son lo suficientemente geniales para salir con ella. Pero en un intento desesperado por tener onda, terminan arruinando el concierto.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: Cortando Camino
added.description: Ben habla con Geezer Bob para hacer alguna tarea de jardín y así ganar un poco de dinero, pero cuando Ben se transforma en Upgrade para convertir la podadora de césped en una cortadora súper rápida, por accidente despierta la ira de los vecinos gnomos de Bob: los diminutos y aterradoramente obstinados duendes de Billy Bob.

added.title: Baila Reynaldo Baila
added.description: Vic está desesperado por ganar el premio en efectivo para el concurso de baile en Monte Macabro y está frustrado porque Val, su pareja, no le deja tomar todas las decisiones. Por eso, elige un compañero diferente: Reynaldo. Pero Vic presiona demasiado a Reynaldo para hacer realidad su visión artística. Al final, Vic aprende que, para tener éxito, hay que ser socios en igualdad de condiciones.

added.title: Poorbucks
added.description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

added.title: People Pleaser
added.description: Blossom neglects her promise to Bubbles when she takes on too many things leaving Buttercup and Bubbles to fend for themselves.

added.title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

added.title: Bengeance is Mine
added.description: Vilgax' former lackey Psyphon is elated when his master returns.

added.title: Animo Crackers
added.description: Dr. Animo from the future comes back to the present to help himself defeat Ben once and for all. (Introducing new Ben alien, Gutrot.)

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Catfight
added.description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

added.title: Pantro robado
added.description: Buitro tiene un nuevo invento, pero hay un gran problema: ile robó la idea a Pantro! Ah, y además Buitro usa su invento para apoderarse del Tercer Planeta. De modo que hay dos grandes problemas.

added.title: La Broma
added.description: Cuando intenta demostrarles a los Thundercachorros que no es un adulto aburrido (como Tigro), León-O ignora sus instintos y se mete con un cristal claramente malvado.

added.title: Manzana Mandona
added.description: Manzana queda a cargo de la Tienda de Dolar por primera vez.

added.title: El secreto del unicornio
added.description: Un unicornio que llora aparece en el Cubil Felino y, entre lágrimas, les dice a los Thundercats que todos sus amigos unicornios han sido capturados. Tigro se cree un experto en el tema que podrá ayudar al último de los unicornios...Solo necesita que deje de llorar lo suficiente para decirle quién se llevó a sus amigos. Es más fácil decirlo que hacerlo, viejo.

added.title: Taladro
added.description: Pantro se está hartando de tener que arreglar cosas constantemente por todo el Cubil Felino, lo cual es una pena porque los Thundercats están a punto de ser atacados por un robot perforador imparable...ique va a romper todo!

added.title: A Esquivar
added.description: iAxel abraza el espíritu del dodgeball para detener la batalla de Madcap y la princesa SugarSalt sobre quién es el mejor villano que se derrama en la discusión de Zoe y Cleo sobre quién es el mejor entrenador!

added.title: Joyride
added.description: iEn una venta de artículos usados ​​con el tío Andrew, Axel y Zoe deben evitar que Madcap convierta su juguete tanque perdido, Joyride, en un agente de caos!

added.title: Sofa Cama
added.description: Cuando los Piratas del Cielo se infiltran en el cuartel general del sheriff, iponen en peligro a los héroes!

added.title: Trampa de Arena
added.description: iAxel y el equipo se dirigen a las dunas del desierto de un cajón de arena en el patio de juegos mientras Madcap intenta desenterrar un ejército de Spy Lizards de la misma línea que Galileo!

added.title: El Mejor Equipo
added.description: Cuando Madcap y sus secuaces chocan un derby de caja de jabón, el equipo debe detener a los malos y ayudar a Axel, atrapado en un automóvil con Luka, a cruzar la línea de meta.

added.title: El Desnudo de Mao Mao
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao pierde la ropa mientras intenta escalar el Rubí Puro Corazón, tiene que regresar al cuartel general antes de que amanezca.

added.title: Revienta Fiestas
added.description: Los planes de la fiesta de Manzana y Cebollín son interrumpidos por un invitado malhumorado.

added.title: La invasion de las guerreras amazonas
added.description: El Tercer Planeta está siendo invadido por Guerreras Amazonas con fuerza y músculos extraordinarios iy parece que los Thundercats son los siguientes en su lista de ataques! Ahora, la seguridad de todos dependerá de los Thundercachorros, aunque sean tan pequeños y las Guerreras Amazonas sean tan grandes.

added.title: Sin Cebollin
added.description: Manzana trata de sobrevivir un fin de semana solo mientras cuida la planta de Cebollín.

added.title: Papel de Bano Bebecin
added.description: Manzana necesita conseguir la provisión del papel higiénico que usaría en toda su vida para terminar su escultura de arte moderno.

added.title: En Suenos
added.description: Los sueños de Steven comienzan a transmitirse en el televisor de su dormitorio.

added.title: Bobbie no Blobbie
added.description: Axel descubre que el culpable del traje mecánico perdido de Bobbie Blobby es Masko, que solo quería limpiar sus cañones de arcilla obstruidos, pero deja que el traje caiga en las manos (o tentáculos) del Dr. Nautilus, icon la intención de inundar las alcantarillas!

added.title: Enfrenta Tus Miedos
added.description: Atrapados en una tienda de mascotas, Manzana y Cebollín deben enfrentarse a sus miedos para poder evitar que Papa Frita se enfrente a los suyos.

added.title: Custody Battle/City of Nutsville
added.description: Custody Battle: Mojo discovers the Rowdyruff Boys are back and is determined to show them that he is a more evil dad than Him./The City of Nutsville: The squirrels of Townsville are chirping mad! But when Bubbles loses her ability to speak a squirrel, the girls don't know how to calm the rodents down.

added.title: Curses/Bang for Your Buck
added.description: Curses: When Bubbles overhears the Professor saying some bad words, the girls add a whole new slew of adjectives to their vocabulary./Bang for Your Buck: When the girls and the Gangreen Gang discover a destructo ray for sale at Mojo's Yard Sale, each team sets out to see who can earn the most money and buy it first.

added.title: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs/Mizzen in Action
added.description: Crazy Mixed Up Puffs: The girls must literally work as one to try and stop Mojo from destroying Townsville./Mizzen in Action: Captain Crack McGraigen and his crew are tossed forward in time where discover the chemical X that marks the spot and it is up to the girls and Professor to send the super-charged pirates back to their own time.

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Mo' Linguish/Oops, I Did It Again
added.description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops, I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Moral Decay/Meet the Beat Alls
added.description: Moral Decay: When Bubbles loses a tooth, she gets a shiny coin under her pillow the next day. Buttercup sees a gold mine in the mouths of Townsville's criminal element./Meet the Beat Alls: Mojo, Him, Princess and Fuzzy band together to form the Bad Four, a criminal supergroup out to destroy the Powerpuff Girls. Everything is going great until Mojo meets Moko Jono and falls in love.

added.title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
added.description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

added.title: Squirreled Domination
added.description: Rare food enthusiast Fud sends the Warriors on a mission to the Deepest Darkest Woods to gather five golden acorns from a golden oak tree for a golden acorn casserole, but poor Vambre has a secret fear of squirrels, and it turns out that golden squirrels are the scariest of them all!

added.title: Surely You Jest-O
added.description: House sitting for Omnibus is boring work for the Warriors, but their decision to allow Jest-O and his Taunting Jester Magisword come in from the rain to entertain them turns out to be their worst idea yet!

added.title: Flirty Phantom
added.description: Lost in Transylberia, the Warriors come to a haunted house for help and meet a young ghost lady inside that wants to spend the rest of her afterlife with Prohyas!

added.title: The Wrath of Neddy
added.description: After Neddy the Mallet easily sails through all the obstacles in the Cave of Stuff he decides to stay as King Neddy, displacing the Cave Weirdos who beg the Warriors to help them reclaim their cave.

added.title: Felonious Prose
added.description: The Warrior mission of finding a lost contact lens gets seriously compromised from Vambre's obsession with the latest Veronica Victorious novel.
